The paper deals with the problem of semantic visual navigation, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO) that involves using visual information to navigate through an environment. The paper also heavily relies on computer vision techniques such as segmentation and detection masks, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.CV. Additionally, the paper proposes using deep learning to learn navigation policies, which falls under the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also mentions using natural language processing techniques to interpret user commands, which could potentially fall under the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
